 for bestpractices and # Search & Filter Functionality

## Overview
Implement a robust, scalable search and filtering system that enables users to locate and drill into content across multiple domains (projects, decisions, templates, and files) with multi-faceted filters, fast performance on large data sets, autocomplete, saved searches, and seamless integration with existing pages (Dashboard, Project Workspace, Templates Library, Drawings & Specs Library). The feature should support full-text search (Elasticsearch/Algolia or PostgreSQL full-text), multi-criteria filtering (status, assignee, date range, project, tags), pagination, and efficient UX for both desktop and mobile.

## Components to Build
- Multi-domain Search Engine
  - Full-text search index (Elasticsearch/Algolia or PostgreSQL tsvector)
  - Data ingestion pipelines from Projects, Decisions, Templates, and Files
  - Result ranking rules and relevancy tuning
- Filters Panel
  - Status filter (Published, Pending, In Review, Declined, Completed, etc.)
  - Assignee filter (users assigned to decisions or templates)
  - Date range filter (created/updated/decision date)
  - Project filter (select from active projects)
  - Tags filter (multi-select, tag chips)
  - Content type selector (Projects, Decisions, Templates, Drawings/Specs)
- Autocomplete & Suggestions
  - Real-time query suggestions
  - Quick filters and recent searches
- Saved Searches & Templates
  - Persist user-specific saved search configurations
  - Shareable saved searches (optional)
- Pagination & Performance Layer
  - Cursor-based or offset-based pagination with page size options
  - Result caching for repeated queries
- Results Grid / List View
  - Cards or list items with essential context: title, snippet, status badge, assignee, project, date, and quick actions
  - Faceted highlights and keyboard navigation
- Quick Attach & Quick Actions
  - From search results, attach decision context to decisions, templates, or client shares
- UI Components
  - Reusable search bar with autosuggest
  - Filter chips, date pickers, multi-select dropdowns
  - Result skeletons and empty state messaging
- Accessibility & Internationalization
  - Keyboard navigable, ARIA attributes, i18n-ready strings

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Search Interface
  - Prominent full-width search bar with left icon, auto-complete, and inline suggestions
  - Clear filters button and responsive filter panel (collapsible on small viewports)
  - Tabs or segmented control to select content type (Projects, Decisions, Templates, Drawings/Specs)
  - Infinite or paginated results with smooth scrolling
- Filters UI
  - Multi-select dropdowns for projects and tags
  - Date range picker with quick presets (Last 7/30/90 days, This Month, Custom)
  - Status badges displayed in results and filters
  - Assignee picker with search and avatar chips
- Results Presentation
  - Card/Grid layout with title, snippet, project association, status badge, assignee, date
  - Highlight matched terms in results
  - Quick actions: Open, Attach to Decision, Save, Share (as applicable)
- Saved Searches
  - UI to save current filters and query with a name; options to share or private
- Accessibility
  - Keyboard shortcuts (e.g., / to focus search), ARIA roles, appropriate contrast, visible focus states
- Performance
  - Debounced queries (e.g., 200-300ms) to avoid excessive requests
  - Prefetch commonly used filters for faster UX
- Responsiveness
  - Desktop: 3–4 column density; Mobile: single-column with sticky filters

### Backend
- Data Models
  - Indexable entities: Project, Decision, Template, File (Drawings/Specs)
  - SearchIndex document: id, type, title, snippet, content, project_id, status, assignee_id, tags, date_fields, full_text
  - SavedSearch: user_id, name, query_payload, filters, content_type, created_at, updated_at
- Search Engine
  - If using Elasticsearch/Algolia:
    - Indexing strategy per entity type with common fields for cross-type search
    - Custom analyzers for domain-specific terms (design terminology, file types)
  - If using PostgreSQL full-text:
    - tsvector fields for content and concatenated search vectors
    - GIN indexes on to_tsvector content and associated fields
  - Relevance tuning: boost project/title/snippet fields; keyword boosts for exact matches
- APIs
  - POST /api/search/query
    - Body: { query: string, filters: { content_types[], status[], assignees[], projects[], tags[], dateRange { from, to } }, page: int, pageSize: int, sort?: { field, order } }
    - Response: { total, page, pageSize, results: [ { id, type, title, snippet, project, status, assignee, date, highlights } ] }
  - GET /api/search/autocomplete?q=..., content_types[]
    - Response: { suggestions: [string], topHits: [ { id, type, title } ] }
  - POST /api/search/save
    - Body: { name, payload: queryPayload }
    - Creates a SavedSearch; returns savedSearchId
  - GET /api/search/save/{id}
    - Retrieve saved search
  - POST /api/search/attach
    - Body: { resultId, targetType, targetId } // attach a search result to a decision/template/drawing
- Database Tables / Indexes
  - entities: projects, decisions, templates, files (drawings/specs)
  - search_index (document_id, type, title, snippet, content, project_id, status, assignee_id, tags, created_at, updated_at)
  - saved_searches (id, user_id, name, payload, content_type, created_at, updated_at)
  - indexes: GIN (search_index) for tsvector fields; appropriate FK constraints
- Security
  - Authentication: OAuth2/JWT or session-based; all search endpoints require authentication
  - Authorization: Ensure users can only search within accessible projects and tenants
  - Rate limiting on search endpoints; audit logging for saved searches
- Validation
  - Validate query string length; reject empty or whitespace-only queries with friendly guidance
  - Validate date ranges (from <= to)
  - Validate content_types against allowed values
  - Validate user-provided IDs for assignees, projects, tags
- Logging & Monitoring
  - Metrics for search latency, error rates, result counts
  - Instrument with tracing for slow queries
- Data Evolution
  - Backfill existing data into search_index on first run or on a scheduled job

### Integration
- Page Connections
  - Dashboard: Add global search banner and quick-access results panel; enable saved searches
  - Project Workspace: Contextual search scoped to the current project with project filter preselected
  - Templates Library: Searchable templates with type = Template; quick apply actions
  - Drawings & Specs Library: Searchable drawings/specs with versioning and quick attach options
- Event Flow
  - User enters query → frontend sends to /api/search/query → backend queries index → results returned with highlights
  - User applies filters → query payload updated → backend returns new results
  - User saves search → /api/search/save stores payload; UI confirms
  - User attaches a result → /api/search/attach links the result to a target entity
- Data Flow & Caching
  - Cache popular searches or results in Redis; invalidate on data changes
  - Real-time suggestions from autocomplete service

## User Experience Flow
1. User lands on the Search & Filter interface (accessible from Dashboard and global header).
2. User types a query in the prominent search bar; autocomplete suggestions appear below.
3. User selects content type tab (Projects, Decisions, Templates, Drawings/Specs) or keeps multi-type results.
4. User applies filters: status, assignee, date range, project(s), and tags; filters update results in real-time (debounced).
5. Results render as cards/list with highlights on matched terms; each item shows title, snippet, project, status, assignee, and date; actions include Open, Attach, or Save.
6. User navigates pages (pagination) or switches to grid/list density; results refresh smoothly.
7. User saves a common set of filters as a Saved Search for quick recall; optionally share with teammates.
8. User utilizes autocomplete to refine search or explores top hits; optionally uses quick attach to link a result to a decision or template.
9. From Drawings & Specs Library or Templates Library, user searches and then attaches results directly to relevant decisions via the search results UI.
10. System tracks search analytics, latency, and saved search usage for optimization.

## Technical Specifications
- Data Models: 
  - Entity tables: projects, decisions, templates, files (drawings/specs)
  - SearchIndex document: { id, type, title, snippet, content, project_id, status, assignee_id, tags, created_at, updated_at, version, workspace_id }
  - SavedSearch: { id, user_id, name, payload(JSON), content_type, created_at, updated_at, last_used_at }
- API Endpoints:
  - POST /api/search/query
  - GET /api/search/autocomplete
  - POST /api/search/save
  - GET /api/search/save/{id}
  - POST /api/search/attach
- Security:
  - Authenticate all endpoints
  - Authorize access to data to ensure user can view within permitted projects
  - Input validation and sanitization
- Validation:
  - Query string length >= 2 characters (unless autocomplete)
  - Date range validation (from <= to)
  - Filters must be arrays or null
  - IDs must exist and be accessible by user
- Performance:
  - Relevance-based ranking with customizable boost factors
  - Batched requests and pagination
  - Optional caching for repeated saved searches
- Accessibility:
  - All interactive elements accessible via keyboard; screen reader friendly labels
- Internationalization:
  - Text keys stored for translations; date formats localized

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Full-text search returns results across Projects, Decisions, Templates, and Drawings/Specs with accurate relevancy and highlights
- [ ] Filters function independently and in combination with multi-select capabilities; date range and tag filters work correctly
- [ ] Autocomplete provides relevant suggestions and top hits within 200-300ms
- [ ] Pagination handles large result sets with stable ordering and correct page counts
- [ ] Saved Searches can be created, retrieved, and invoked; saved filters persist user preferences
- [ ] Quick Attach from search results to decisions/templates/drawings works and updates related entities
- [ ] UI adheres to the design system: cards, typography, spacing, and color usage as specified
- [ ] Security: authenticated access enforced; users only access allowed data
- [ ] Performance: average search latency under 150ms for small datasets and under 300ms for large datasets under typical load

## UI/UX Guidelines
