=== TASK ===
# Search & Filter Functionality

## Overview
Implement a robust, scalable search and filtering system that enables users to locate and drill into content across multiple domains (projects, decisions, templates, and files) with multi-faceted filters, fast performance on large data sets, autocomplete, saved searches, and seamless integration with existing pages (Dashboard, Project Workspace, Templates Library, Drawings & Specs Library). The feature should support full-text search (Elasticsearch/Algolia or PostgreSQL full-text), multi-criteria filtering (status, assignee, date range, project, tags), pagination, and efficient UX for both desktop and mobile.

## Components to Build
- Multi-domain Search Engine
  - Full-text search index (Elasticsearch/Algolia or PostgreSQL tsvector)
  - Data ingestion pipelines from Projects, Decisions, Templates, and Files
  - Result ranking rules and relevancy tuning
- Filters Panel
  - Status filter (Published, Pending, In Review, Declined, Completed, etc.)
  - Assignee filter (users assigned to decisions or templates)
  - Date range filter (created/updated/decision date)
  - Project filter (select from active projects)
  - Tags filter (multi-select, tag chips)
  - Content type selector (Projects, Decisions, Templates, Drawings/Specs)
- Autocomplete & Suggestions
  - Real-time query suggestions
  - Quick filters and recent searches
- Saved Searches & Templates
  - Persist user-specific saved search configurations
  - Shareable saved searches (optional)
- Pagination & Performance Layer
  - Cursor-based or offset-based pagination with page size options
  - Result caching for repeated queries
- Results Grid / List View
  - Cards or list items with essential context: title, snippet, status badge, assignee, project, date, and quick actions
  - Faceted highlights and keyboard navigation
- Quick Attach & Quick Actions
  - From search results, attach decision context to decisions, templates, or client shares
- UI Components
  - Reusable search bar with autosuggest
  - Filter chips, date pickers, multi-select dropdowns
  - Result skeletons and empty state messaging
- Accessibility & Internationalization
  - Keyboard navigable, ARIA attributes, i18n-ready strings

